data.title: Katholische Kirche St. Stephanus, Sausenheim
data.meta_description: The Catholic Church is one of two churches in the Grünstadt district of Sausenheim. It dates from the 12th and 13th centuries.
data.text:
The Catholic Church is one of two churches in the Gr√ºnstadt district of Sausenheim. It dates from the 12th and 13th centuries.

the Catholic Church of St. Stephan dates partly from the 12th and 13th centuries (tower and basement) and partly from the 14th century (Gothic choir and Katharinen chapel) and the nave is neo-Gothic from 1888. Worth seeing: 15th century sacraments .; 4 wooden figures 1440; Sanstein altar, late baroque, 1728
